b'       INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY  MADRAS Academic Section  Circular No. 12A/JM2016/B2/2016;&n;bsp; &nbs;p;&nbsp;Dated 07.04.2016   Sub: Dual Degree & M.Tech. Project  Reg.  The resolution of the Senate at its 255 th  The project work of all Dual Degree/M.Tech. students will commence not later than 1 st  June, following the 8 th  / 2 nd  semester respectively, regardless of whether the student is eligible for HTTA or not.  As per the MHRD letter no. 172/2014TS1, dated 18.02.2015 and 01.09.2015, the leave entitlement of the students who are receiving HTTA is as follows:  All Dual Degree / M.Tech. Students are eligible for 8 days causal leave and 15 days vacation leave starting from 1 st  of July following the 8 th  semester/2 nd  semester, to the end of the programme. The holidays in any contiguous leave period will also be counted against leave.  Sd/  Deputy Registrar (Courses) To All Students thro  student@list.iitm.ac.in All Faculty Members thro  faculty@list.iitm.ac.in  '

